If MHD_ASAN_POISON_ACTIVE is defined but neither HAVE___ASAN_REGION_IS_POISONED nor HAVE___ASAN_ADDRESS_IS_POISONED is defined, need_red_zone_before is unconditionally set to true (need_red_zone_before = true;) so the controlling expression if (need_red_zone_before) is effectively invariant (always true). This is not an allowed exception (not an intentional infinite loop), so Rule 14.3 is violated in that configuration.
